      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "If we were compiled without ECDSA verification I believe we would have no use for a scalar negate in the library at all.\r\n\r\nProbably your \"blinded signature scheme\" is insecure.  I'd actually take a sizable bet because essentially every description I've seen of ECC blind signing I've seen online was insecure as described (and also failed to even mention the risks).\r\n\r\nIf getting access to some libsecp256k1 internal is getting in your way, then you probably have a more serious problem you're not even aware of...  this is part of the reason for our motivation in not offering a grabbag of low level primitives.  If you'd like to implement blind signing against the schnorr PRs in the repo, I'd be happy to review them. Blind signing is among the operations I'd like to see the library provide for it...",
